{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882516484,"sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad8b49e001rUYx7Sr4tnx0mC","messageID":"msg_d7ad8ab21001v41YRIU38TzJl9","sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0ecd0d5214c84716b691128d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-020\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n25: \n26: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n31: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n32: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n33: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n38: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n39: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n40: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n45: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n46: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n51: - **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n57: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n63: \n64: The system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n69: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n71: - **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n76: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n78: - **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n83: - **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n85:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n86:   - `port`: `8080`\n87:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n88:   - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n93: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n95:   - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n96:   - `--language` overrides `language`\n97:   - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n98:   - `--port` overrides `port`\n99:   - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n100:   - `--description` overrides `description`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n105: \n106: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n111: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n113: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n118: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n120: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n125: - **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n127: - **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n132: \n133: The system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n138: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n139: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n144: - **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n145: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n150: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n156: \n157: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n162: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n163: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n168: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n174: - **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n180: \n181: The system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n186: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n187:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n188:   - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n189:   - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n190:   - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n191:   - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n192:   - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n193:   - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n194:   - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n195:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n200: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n201: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n202: - **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n207: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n208: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n209: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n214: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n215: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n216: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n221: \n222: The system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n225: \n226: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n227: - **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n228: - **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n233: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n234: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n239: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n240: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n245: \n246: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n251: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n252: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n253: - **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n258: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n260: - **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Acceptance Criteria\n265: \n266: - [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n267: - [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n268: - [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n269: - [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n270: - [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n271: - [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n272: - [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n273: - [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n274: - [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n275: - [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Architecture Notes\n280: \n281: ### Key Components\n282: \n283: | Component | Path | Description |\n284: |-----------|------|-------------|\n285: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n286: | PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n287: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n288: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n289: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n290: \n291: ### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n292: \n293: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n294: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n295: | agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n296: | language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n297: | entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n298: | port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n299: | build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n300: | description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n301: | requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n302: \n303: ### CLI Options Mapping\n304: \n305: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n306: |------------|----------------|------|\n307: | `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n308: | `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n309: | `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n310: | `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n311: | `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n312: | `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n313: | `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: # Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n318: \n319: ## Overview\n320: \n321: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n322: \n323: ## Base Specifications\n324: \n325: - **AR**: AR-038\n326: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n327: - **Language**: Go\n328: - **Size**: L\n329: \n330: ## Reference\n331: \n332: Base spec: client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ## Background\n337: \n338: The workloadmanager module provides workload management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. It includes:\n339: - WorkloadManager interface for CRUD operations\n340: - GC (Garbage Collection) worker for expired resource cleanup\n341: - Expiration checker for TTL and idle timeout\n342: - Graceful manager for connection draining\n343: - Cleanup manager for orphaned resources\n344: - Batch manager for bulk operations\n345: - HTTP server with REST API endpoints\n346: \n347: ---\n348: \n349: ## Requirements\n350: \n351: ### Feature: CleanupManager Resource Cleanup\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-A — CleanupManager deletes orphaned services\n354: \n355: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n356: - **WHEN** cleanupServices is called with a namespace and owner reference\n357: - **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned service resource strings\n358: - **AND** services with matching owner references should be deleted\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-B — CleanupManager deletes orphaned configmaps\n361: \n362: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n363: - **WHEN** cleanupConfigMaps is called with a namespace and owner reference\n364: - **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned configmap resource strings\n365: - **AND** configmaps with the annotation `agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete=true` and matching owner should be deleted\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-C — CleanupManager handles retained PVCs\n368: \n369: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n370: - **WHEN** cleanupPVCs is called with a namespace and owner reference for a PVC with Retain policy\n371: - **THEN** the PVC should not be deleted\n372: - **AND** other PVCs with matching owner should be deleted\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-D — CleanupManager cleans orphaned resources\n375: \n376: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager and a Sandbox object\n377: - **WHEN** cleanupOrphanedResources is called\n378: - **THEN** it should clean services, configmaps, and PVCs associated with the sandbox\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-E — CleanupManager finds orphaned services\n381: \n382: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n383: - **WHEN** FindOrphanedServices is called with namespace and sessionID\n384: - **THEN** it should return service names that have no owner references\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-F — CleanupManager CleanupAllResources\n387: \n388: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n389: - **WHEN** CleanupAllResources is called with a sandbox\n390: - **THEN** it should clean all associated resources\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Feature: BatchManager Operations\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-A — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes synchronously under threshold\n397: \n398: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n399: - **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with fewer than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n400: - **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes synchronously\n401: - **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with deleted and failed counts\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-B — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes asynchronously over threshold\n404: \n405: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n406: - **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with more than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n407: - **THEN** it should start async deletion in background\n408: - **AND** return immediately with all items marked as deleted\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-C — BatchManager deletes stale sandboxes\n411: \n412: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n413: - **WHEN** deleteStaleSandboxes is called\n414: - **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes in Unknown or Failed state older than StaleStateThreshold (1 hour)\n415: - **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with results\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-D — BatchManager deletes by label selector\n418: \n419: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n420: - **WHEN** handleDeleteByLabelSelector is called with a label selector\n421: - **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes matching the label selector\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-E — BatchManager public methods\n424: \n425: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager\n426: - **WHEN** DeleteAllInNamespace, DeleteByLabelSelector, or DeleteStaleSandboxes are called\n427: - **THEN** they should delegate to the appropriate handler methods\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ### Feature: WorkloadManager Sandbox Operations\n432: \n433: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-A — GetSandboxBySessionID finds AgentRuntime\n434: \n435: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime resources\n436: - **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in an AgentRuntime\n437: - **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n438: \n439: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-B — GetSandboxBySessionID finds CodeInterpreter\n440: \n441: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter resources\n442: - **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in a CodeInterpreter\n443: - **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-C — GetSandboxBySessionID returns error when not found\n446: \n447: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n448: - **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a non-existent sessionID\n449: - **THEN** it should return ErrSandboxNotFound\n450: \n451: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-D — DeleteSandbox deletes AgentRuntime by sessionId\n452: \n453: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime with matching sessionId label\n454: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n455: - **THEN** it should delete the matching AgentRuntime\n456: - **AND** return nil on success\n457: \n458: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-E — DeleteSandbox deletes CodeInterpreter by sessionId\n459: \n460: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label\n461: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n462: - **THEN** it should delete the matching CodeInterpreter\n463: - **AND** return nil on success\n464: \n465: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-F — DeleteSandbox applies force delete\n466: \n467: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n468: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with Force=true\n469: - **THEN** it should set GracePeriodSeconds to 0\n470: \n471: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-G — DeleteSandbox applies label selector\n472: \n473: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n474: - **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with LabelSelector\n475: - **THEN** it should use the label selector when listing resources\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: AR-038-003-H — ListSandboxes returns combined list\n478: \n479: - **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n480: - **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called with namespace and ListOptions\n481: - **THEN** it should return a SandboxList containing both types\n482: - **AND** apply label and field selectors correctly\n483: \n484: ---\n485: \n486: ### Feature: Server HTTP Handlers\n487: \n488: #### Scenario: AR-038-004-A — Server health check endpoint\n489: \n490: - **GIVEN** a Server instance\n491: - **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n492: - **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with \"ok\"\n493: \n494: #### Scenario: AR-038-004-B — Server readiness check - ready\n495: \n496: - **GIVEN** a Server with ready=true\n497: - **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n498: - **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with status \"ok\"\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: AR-038-004-C — Server readiness check - not ready\n501: \n502: - **GIVEN** a Server with ready=false\n503: - **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n504: - **THEN** it should return HTTP 503 with status \"not ready\"\n505: \n506: #### Scenario: AR-038-004-D — Server starts and stops cleanly\n507: \n508: - **GIVEN** a Server with valid config\n509: - **WHEN** Start() is called\n510: - **THEN** it should bind to the configured port\n511: - **AND** Start() should return nil\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: AR-038-004-E — Server handles API error mapping\n514: \n515: - **GIVEN** a Server with a WorkloadManager that returns an error\n516: - **WHEN** handleError is called with k8s IsNotFound error\n517: - **THEN** it should return HTTP 404 with reason \"NotFound\"\n518: \n519: #### Scenario: AR-038-004-F — Server corsMiddleware sets headers\n520: \n521: - **GIVEN** a Server\n522: - **WHEN** corsMiddleware processes a request\n523: - **THEN** it should set Access-Control-Allow-* headers\n524: - **AND** handle OPTIONS preflight requests\n525: \n526: ---\n527: \n528: ### Feature: GracefulManager Operations\n529: \n530: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-A — GracefulManager registers connection\n531: \n532: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n533: - **WHEN** RegisterConnection is called with a sandboxID\n534: - **THEN** the active connection count should increment\n535: \n536: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-B — GracefulManager unregisters connection\n537: \n538: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with an active connection\n539: - **WHEN** UnregisterConnection is called with the sandboxID\n540: - **THEN** the active connection count should decrement\n541: \n542: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-C — GracefulManager drains connections\n543: \n544: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n545: - **WHEN** drainConnections is called with a sandboxID\n546: - **THEN** the draining flag should be set to true\n547: \n548: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-D — GracefulManager checks if draining\n549: \n550: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox marked for draining\n551: - **WHEN** IsDraining is called with the sandboxID\n552: - **THEN** it should return true\n553: \n554: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-E — GracefulManager gets active connections\n555: \n556: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with registered connections\n557: - **WHEN** GetActiveConnections is called\n558: - **THEN** it should return the correct count\n559: \n560: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-F — GracefulManager cleans up sandbox state\n561: \n562: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox\n563: - **WHEN** Cleanup is called with the sandboxID\n564: - **THEN** the sandbox entry should be removed from connections map\n565: \n566: #### Scenario: AR-038-005-G — GracefulManager waitForConnections timeout\n567: \n568: - **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with active connections that never drain\n569: - **WHEN** waitForConnections is called with a short timeout\n570: - **THEN** it should return an error after timeout\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ### Feature: K8sClient Initialization\n575: \n576: #### Scenario: AR-038-006-A — K8sClient NewK8sClient with kubeconfig path\n577: \n578: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig path\n579: - **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with the path\n580: - **THEN** it should return a K8sClient with Clientset, KubernetesClient, and DynamicClient\n581: - **AND** return nil error\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: AR-038-006-B — K8sClient NewK8sClient with in-cluster mode\n584: \n585: - **GIVEN** InClusterMode constant\n586: - **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with InClusterMode\n587: - **THEN** it should attempt in-cluster config\n588: \n589: #### Scenario: AR-038-006-C — K8sClient NewInClusterClient\n590: \n591: - **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes cluster\n592: - **WHEN** NewInClusterClient is called\n593: - **THEN** it should create clients using in-cluster config\n594: \n595: #### Scenario: AR-038-006-D — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles tilde\n596: \n597: - **GIVEN** a path starting with ~\n598: - **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n599: - **THEN** it should replace ~ with the home directory\n600: \n601: #### Scenario: AR-038-006-E — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles empty path\n602: \n603: - **GIVEN** an empty string\n604: - **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n605: - **THEN** it should return the empty string\n606: \n607: ---\n608: \n609: ### Feature: Type Helper Functions\n610: \n611: #### Scenario: AR-038-007-A — NewAPIResponse creates correct response\n612: \n613: - **GIVEN** data and metadata\n614: - **WHEN** NewAPIResponse is called\n615: - **THEN** it should return an APIResponse with Status=\"Success\"\n616: \n617: #### Scenario: AR-038-007-B — NewAPIError creates correct error\n618: \n619: - **GIVEN** message, reason, and code\n620: - **WHEN** NewAPIError is called\n621: - **THEN** it should return an APIError with Status=\"Failure\"\n622: \n623: #### Scenario: AR-038-007-C — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps running state\n624: \n625: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Running condition\n626: - **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n627: - **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n628: \n629: #### Scenario: AR-038-007-D — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps failed state\n630: \n631: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Failed condition\n632: - **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n633: - **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateFailed\n634: \n635: #### Scenario: AR-038-007-E — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps deleting state\n636: \n637: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp\n638: - **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n639: - **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateDeleting\n640: \n641: #### Scenario: AR-038-007-F — sandboxFromCodeInterpreter maps running state\n642: \n643: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with Ready=true\n644: - **WHEN** sandboxFromCodeInterpreter is called\n645: - **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n646: \n647: ---\n648: \n649: ### Feature: ListExpiredSandboxes\n650: \n651: #### Scenario: AR-038-008-A — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired AgentRuntimes\n652: \n653: - **GIVEN** a client with AgentRuntime resources\n654: - **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n655: - **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n656: \n657: #### Scenario: AR-038-008-B — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired CodeInterpreters\n658: \n659: - **GIVEN** a client with CodeInterpreter resources\n660: - **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n661: - **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n662: \n663: #### Scenario: AR-038-008-C — ListExpiredSandboxes handles empty namespace\n664: \n665: - **GIVEN** a client with resources in a namespace\n666: - **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with an empty namespace string\n667: - **THEN** it should list all expired sandboxes\n668: \n669: ---\n670: \n671: ### Feature: Retry Logic\n672: \n673: #### Scenario: AR-038-009-A — Retry with exponential backoff\n674: \n675: - **GIVEN** a function that fails initially then succeeds\n676: - **WHEN** retry logic is applied\n677: - **THEN** it should retry with increasing delays\n678: - **AND** ultimately succeed\n679: \n680: #### Scenario: AR-038-009-B — Retry stops after max attempts\n681: \n682: - **GIVEN** a function that always fails\n683: - **WHEN** retry logic is applied with max attempts\n684: - **THEN** it should return the last error after exhausting retries\n685: \n686: ---\n687: \n688: ## Acceptance Criteria\n689: \n690: - [ ] AC001: All CleanupManager methods must have unit tests covering success and error paths\n691: - [ ] AC002: All BatchManager methods must have tests with mocked WorkloadManager\n692: - [ ] AC003: WorkloadManager sandbox operations must have tests with fake clients\n693: - [ ] AC004: Server HTTP handlers must have tests using httptest\n694: - [ ] AC005: GracefulManager connection tracking must have unit tests\n695: - [ ] AC006: K8sClient initialization must have tests for different config modes\n696: - [ ] AC007: Helper functions (NewAPIResponse, NewAPIError, sandboxFrom*) must have tests\n697: - [ ] AC008: ListExpiredSandboxes must have tests for both resource types\n698: - [ ] AC009: Retry logic must have unit tests for backoff behavior\n699: - [ ] AC010: Existing tests in service_test.go, gc_test.go, expiration_test.go remain passing\n700: \n701: ---\n702: \n703: ## Test File Status\n704: \n705: | Source File | Test File | Status |\n706: |-------------|-----------|--------|\n707: | service.go | service_test.go | Complete |\n708: | gc.go | gc_test.go | Complete |\n709: | expiration.go | expiration_test.go | Complete |\n710: | cleanup.go | cleanup_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n711: | server.go | server_test.go | Complete |\n712: | graceful.go | graceful_test.go | Complete |\n713: | batch.go | batch_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n714: | client.go | client_test.go | Complete |\n715: | delete_test.go | N/A | Exists |\n716: | retry.go | retry_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n717: \n718: ---\n719: \n720: ## References\n721: \n722: - Client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n723: - API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n724: - Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter\n\n(End of file - total 724 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882516472,"end":1775882516480}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775882516508,"sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad8b803001gSev5vN0i3exHH","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ad8ab21001v41YRIU38TzJl9","sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":37203,"input":1864,"output":77,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":35262}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775882519424,"sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad8c37e0010Ct3Q6cNW50Yxo","messageID":"msg_d7ad8b8360011DryKksLYkIxEq","sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882602637,"sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad8c951001o8jKhgSjWmTKT8","messageID":"msg_d7ad8b8360011DryKksLYkIxEq","sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_85a43e749c71435fb2c82f60","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-039\n- **Module**: `pkg`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n\n1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT\n2. **pkg/store**: Valkey/Redis-backed session and sandbox storage\n3. **pkg/picod**: Pico execution server with command execution and file handling\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Initialization and Configuration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-A — Router creates with default config\n\n- **GIVEN** a nil config is passed to `NewRouter`\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with default configuration values\n- **AND** default listen address is \":8080\"\n- **AND** backend timeout is 30 seconds\n- **AND** rate limiting is disabled by default\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-B — Router creates with custom config\n\n- **GIVEN** a Config with SessionEnabled=true and JWTEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with SessionManager initialized\n- **AND** JWTManager is initialized\n- **AND** SessionHandler is registered for /v1/sessions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-C — Router adds and removes backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a Router instance is created\n- **WHEN** `AddBackend(\"backend1\", \"http://localhost:8081\", \"/api\", \"backend-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is added to the pool\n- **WHEN** `RemoveBackend(\"backend1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is removed from the pool\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Backend Pool and Health Checking\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-A — Backend pool routes requests\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with multiple backends registered\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a path matching a backend prefix\n- **THEN** the matching backend is returned\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a non-matching path\n- **THEN** nil is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-B — Health checker monitors backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with registered backends\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Start() is invoked\n- **THEN** periodic health checks run at configured interval\n- **WHEN** a backend becomes unhealthy\n- **THEN** the backend is marked as unavailable\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Stop() is invoked\n- **THEN** health checking stops\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Rate Limiting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-A — Rate limiter allows requests under limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=10 and Burst=20\n- **WHEN** 5 requests arrive in quick succession\n- **THEN** all requests are allowed through\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-B — Rate limiter blocks requests over limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=2 and Burst=4\n- **WHEN** 10 requests arrive simultaneously\n- **THEN** requests beyond burst limit are blocked with 429 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-C — Rate limiter can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with enabled=false\n- **WHEN** any number of requests arrive\n- **THEN** all requests pass through without rate limiting\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-A — Authenticator validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=true and AuthToken=\"secret\"\n- **WHEN** request with \"Authorization: Bearer secret\" header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n- **WHEN** request with wrong token arrives\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-B — Authenticator can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=false\n- **WHEN** any request arrives\n- **THEN** request passes through without token validation\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Session Management\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-A — Session manager creates session\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with SessionEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via session store\n- **THEN** session ID is generated\n- **AND** session data is stored with expiry\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-B — Session manager cleanup removes expired sessions\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with sessions in store\n- **WHEN** cleanup runs and finds expired sessions\n- **THEN** expired sessions are removed from store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-C — Session middleware attaches session to request\n\n- **GIVEN** a request with valid session cookie\n- **WHEN** request passes through SessionMiddleware\n- **THEN** session info is available in request context\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - JWT Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-A — JWT manager creates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with HS256 algorithm and secret=\"mysecret\"\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called with user claims\n- **THEN** a signed JWT token is returned\n- **AND** token contains correct issuer and audience\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-B — JWT manager validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with valid secret\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with a valid token\n- **THEN** claims are returned without error\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with an expired token\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating token expiration\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with invalid signature\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid token\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-C — JWT middleware enforces authentication\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTMiddleware with JWTEnabled=true and JWTAllowQueryParam=false\n- **WHEN** request without JWT arrives at protected endpoint\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n- **WHEN** request with valid JWT in Authorization header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed and claims available in context\n- **WHEN** JWTAllowQueryParam=true and JWT in query param\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Logging and Metrics\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-A — Logger records requests\n\n- **GIVEN** Logger middleware is in the chain\n- **WHEN** HTTP request arrives\n- **THEN** request details are logged including method, path, duration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-B — Metrics records request stats\n\n- **GIVEN** Metrics instance\n- **WHEN** `IncBackendRequests(backend, status)` is called\n- **THEN** backend request counter increments\n- **WHEN** `RecordRequestDuration(method, path, backend, duration)` is called\n- **THEN** request duration is recorded\n- **WHEN** `IncErrors(errorType)` is called\n- **THEN** error counter increments\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Store Interface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-008-A — Store interface contract\n\n- **GIVEN** a Store implementation (Valkey or Redis)\n- **WHEN** all interface methods are called\n- **THEN** the Store implements the complete Store interface:\n  - Ping() error\n  - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error\n  - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n  - Close() error\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Valkey Store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-A — Valkey store connects with credentials\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variables VALKEY_ADDR and VALKEY_PASSWORD are set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** a Valkey client connects successfully\n- **AND** ping returns \"PONG\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-B — Valkey store requires address\n\n- **GIVEN** VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-C — Valkey store stores sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo with SessionID and ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is stored in Valkey\n- **AND** session is added to expiry index\n- **AND** session is added to last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-D — Valkey store retrieves sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox was previously stored\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** correct SandboxInfo is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-E — Valkey store returns error for non-existent session\n\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that doesn't exist\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** ErrNotFound is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-F — Valkey store updates sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox data is updated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-G — Valkey store deletes sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n- **AND** session is removed from expiry index\n- **AND** session is removed from last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-H — Valkey store lists expired sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes expiring before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-I — Valkey store lists inactive sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different last activity times\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes inactive before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-J — Valkey store validates input\n\n- **GIVEN** nil sandbox passed to StoreSandbox\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"sandbox is nil\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with empty SessionID\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"session ID is required\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-K — Valkey store updates last activity\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time)` is called\n- **THEN** last activity timestamp is updated in index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-L — Valkey store closes connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey store is connected\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** connection is closed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Server Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-A — Server creates with valid config\n\n- **GIVEN** valid Config and AuthConfig\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** server instance is returned\n- **AND** Gin engine is configured\n- **AND** routes are registered\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-B — Server validates config\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with invalid values (e.g., negative port)\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-C — Server sets workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with Workspace=\"/tmp/test-workspace\"\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** workspace directory is created if not exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-D — Server creates with empty workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with empty Workspace\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** current working directory is used as workspace\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Path Sanitization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-A — Path sanitization allows safe paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"subdir/file.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** resolved path within workspace is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-B — Path sanitization blocks escape attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-C — Path sanitization blocks absolute paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"/etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-D — Path sanitization handles symlinks\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\" and symlink /app/link -> /tmp\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"link/sensitive\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-A — Auth manager loads public key\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthConfig with valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** AuthManager initializes\n- **THEN** public key is loaded successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-B — Auth manager validates JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** valid JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** claims are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-C — Auth manager rejects invalid JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** invalid or expired JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-D — Auth middleware allows public paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to public path like /health\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is allowed without JWT validation\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-E — Auth middleware requires auth for protected paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to protected path /api/execute without token\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Execute Handler\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-A — Execute handler runs valid command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with stdout=\"hello\", ExitCode=0 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-B — Execute handler fails on empty command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with empty Command array\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-C — Execute handler respects timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"sleep\", \"10\"] and Timeout=\"1s\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with ExitCode=124 (timeout) is returned\n- **AND** stderr indicates timeout\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-D — Execute handler validates working directory\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with WorkingDir=\"../../../etc\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-E — Execute handler captures stderr\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"ls\", \"/nonexistent\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response includes stderr output\n- **AND** non-zero ExitCode is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-F — Execute handler accepts custom environment\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"env\"] and Env={\"TEST_VAR\": \"test\"}\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response stdout contains TEST_VAR=test\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - File Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-A — Upload file handler saves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file upload request with valid content\n- **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** file is saved to workspace\n- **AND** success response is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-B — List files handler returns directory contents\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace with multiple files\n- **WHEN** ListFilesHandler is called\n- **THEN** list of files is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-C — Download file handler serves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file exists in workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler is called with path\n- **THEN** file content is served\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-D — Download file handler blocks path escape\n\n- **GIVEN** request for file outside workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** request is rejected\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Health Check and RSA Key Loading\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-A — Health check returns healthy status\n\n- **GIVEN** Server is running\n- **WHEN** GET /health is requested\n- **THEN** response with status \"healthy\" is returned\n- **AND** HTTP 200 status code\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-B — LoadRSAPublicKey parses valid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** *rsa.PublicKey is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-C — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects invalid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** invalid PEM data\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-D — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects non-RSA key\n\n- **GIVEN** PEM data containing non-RSA key\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"public key is not an RSA key\" is returned\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Router Module\n- [ ] AC001: Unit tests for Config initialization and defaults\n- [ ] AC002: Unit tests for Router creation with various config combinations\n- [ ] AC003: Unit tests for BackendPool AddBackend, RemoveBackend, GetBackendForRequest\n- [ ] AC004: Unit tests for HealthChecker Start, Stop, checkBackend\n- [ ] AC005: Unit tests for RateLimiter Allow, Middleware\n- [ ] AC006: Unit tests for Authenticator Middleware with enabled/disabled states\n- [ ] AC007: Unit tests for SessionManager Create, Get, Delete, Cleanup\n- [ ] AC008: Unit tests for JWTManager GenerateToken, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC009: Unit tests for JWTMiddleware with various configurations\n- [ ] AC010: Unit tests for Logger Middleware\n- [ ] AC011: Unit tests for Metrics IncBackendRequests, RecordRequestDuration, IncErrors\n\n### Store Module\n- [ ] AC012: Unit tests for Valkey store connection with mocked client\n- [ ] AC013: Unit tests for StoreSandbox with valid and invalid inputs\n- [ ] AC014: Unit tests for GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existing sessions\n- [ ] AC015: Unit tests for UpdateSandbox\n- [ ] AC016: Unit tests for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n- [ ] AC017: Unit tests for ListExpiredSandboxes\n- [ ] AC018: Unit tests for ListInactiveSandboxes\n- [ ] AC019: Unit tests for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n- [ ] AC020: Unit tests for Close\n\n### Picod Module\n- [ ] AC021: Unit tests for Server creation with valid and invalid configs\n- [ ] AC022: Unit tests for setWorkspace\n- [ ] AC023: Unit tests for sanitizePath with various path inputs\n- [ ] AC024: Unit tests for AuthManager LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC025: Unit tests for auth middleware with public/protected paths\n- [ ] AC026: Unit tests for ExecuteHandler with valid commands, timeout, invalid working dir\n- [ ] AC027: Unit tests for UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler\n- [ ] AC028: Unit tests for HealthCheckHandler\n- [ ] AC029: Unit tests for LoadRSAPublicKey\n- [ ] AC030: Existing tests in router, store, picod packages remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| router/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| router/config.go | config_test.go | Complete |\n| router/route.go | route_test.go | Complete |\n| router/backend.go | backend_test.go | Complete |\n| router/health.go | health_test.go | Complete |\n| router/ratelimit.go | ratelimit_test.go | Complete |\n| router/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| router/session.go | session_test.go | Complete |\n| router/jwt.go | jwt_test.go | Complete |\n| router/logging.go | logging_test.go | Complete |\n| router/metrics.go | (uses existing) | N/A |\n| store/store.go | (interface only) | N/A |\n| store/store_valkey.go | store_valkey_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| store/store_redis.go | store_redis_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/execute.go | execute_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| picod/files.go | files_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/health.go | health_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n- Use interfaces for dependencies (Store, HTTP clients, etc.)\n- Create mock implementations for testing using testify/mock\n- Use gomock or testify.mock for generating mocks\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n- Keep tests in same package as code under test\n- Use `package router` (not `package router_test`)\n\n### Table-Driven Tests\n- Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n- Example pattern:\n```go\ntests := []struct {\n    name    string\n    input   string\n    want    string\n    wantErr bool\n}{...}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- Router module: 70%+ code coverage\n- Store module: 80%+ code coverage\n- Picod module: 70%+ code coverage\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Router module: `pkg/router/`\n- Store module: `pkg/store/`\n- Picod module: `pkg/picod/`\n- Common types: `pkg/common/types/`","oldString":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":51,"character":13},"end":{"line":51,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":52,"character":21},"end":{"line":52,"character":21}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field HealthCheckInterval"},{"range":{"start":{"line":53,"character":20},"end":{"line":53,"character":20}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field HealthCheckTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":54,"character":20},"end":{"line":54,"character":20}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field MaxConnsPerBackend"},{"range":{"start":{"line":57,"character":13},"end":{"line":57,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field AuthEnabled"},{"range":{"start":{"line":58,"character":11},"end":{"line":58,"character":11}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field AuthToken"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/session_middleware.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":179,"character":62},"end":{"line":179,"character":77}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused parameter: r"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/execute.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":156,"character":43},"end":{"line":156,"character":58}},"severity":1,"code":"MissingFieldOrMethod","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#MissingFieldOrMethod"},"source":"compiler","message":"vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method ZaddScoreMember)"},{"range":{"start":{"line":156,"character":66},"end":{"line":156,"character":81}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredImportedName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredImportedName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: valkey.ZaddScoreMember"},{"range":{"start":{"line":157,"character":49},"end":{"line":157,"character":64}},"severity":1,"code":"MissingFieldOrMethod","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#MissingFieldOrMethod"},"source":"compiler","message":"vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ZaddScoreMember undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method ZaddScoreMember)"},{"range":{"start":{"line":157,"character":72},"end":{"line":157,"character":87}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredImportedName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredImportedName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: valkey.ZaddScoreMember"},{"range":{"start":{"line":337,"character":64},"end":{"line":337,"character":69}},"severity":1,"code":"MissingFieldOrMethod","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#MissingFieldOrMethod"},"source":"compiler","message":"vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Score undefined (type cmds.ZaddKey has no field or method Score)"},{"range":{"start":{"line":347,"character":8},"end":{"line":347,"character":22}},"severity":1,"code":"TooManyValues","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#TooManyValues"},"source":"compiler","message":"vs.cli.Close() (no value) used as value"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/server.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1,8 +1,604 @@\n-# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n+# Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n \n ## Overview\n \n+This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n+\n+## Base Specifications\n+\n+- **AR**: AR-039\n+- **Module**: `pkg`\n+- **Language**: Go\n+- **Size**: L\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Background\n+\n+The agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n+\n+1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT\n+2. **pkg/store**: Valkey/Redis-backed session and sandbox storage\n+3. **pkg/picod**: Pico execution server with command execution and file handling\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirements\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - Initialization and Configuration\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-001-A — Router creates with default config\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a nil config is passed to `NewRouter`\n+- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n+- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with default configuration values\n+- **AND** default listen address is \":8080\"\n+- **AND** backend timeout is 30 seconds\n+- **AND** rate limiting is disabled by default\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-001-B — Router creates with custom config\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a Config with SessionEnabled=true and JWTEnabled=true\n+- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n+- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with SessionManager initialized\n+- **AND** JWTManager is initialized\n+- **AND** SessionHandler is registered for /v1/sessions\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-001-C — Router adds and removes backends\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a Router instance is created\n+- **WHEN** `AddBackend(\"backend1\", \"http://localhost:8081\", \"/api\", \"backend-1\")` is called\n+- **THEN** the backend is added to the pool\n+- **WHEN** `RemoveBackend(\"backend1\")` is called\n+- **THEN** the backend is removed from the pool\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - Backend Pool and Health Checking\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-002-A — Backend pool routes requests\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with multiple backends registered\n+- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a path matching a backend prefix\n+- **THEN** the matching backend is returned\n+- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a non-matching path\n+- **THEN** nil is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-002-B — Health checker monitors backends\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with registered backends\n+- **WHEN** HealthChecker Start() is invoked\n+- **THEN** periodic health checks run at configured interval\n+- **WHEN** a backend becomes unhealthy\n+- **THEN** the backend is marked as unavailable\n+- **WHEN** HealthChecker Stop() is invoked\n+- **THEN** health checking stops\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - Rate Limiting\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-003-A — Rate limiter allows requests under limit\n+\n+- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=10 and Burst=20\n+- **WHEN** 5 requests arrive in quick succession\n+- **THEN** all requests are allowed through\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-003-B — Rate limiter blocks requests over limit\n+\n+- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=2 and Burst=4\n+- **WHEN** 10 requests arrive simultaneously\n+- **THEN** requests beyond burst limit are blocked with 429 status\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-003-C — Rate limiter can be disabled\n+\n+- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with enabled=false\n+- **WHEN** any number of requests arrive\n+- **THEN** all requests pass through without rate limiting\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - Authentication\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-004-A — Authenticator validates token\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=true and AuthToken=\"secret\"\n+- **WHEN** request with \"Authorization: Bearer secret\" header arrives\n+- **THEN** request is allowed\n+- **WHEN** request with wrong token arrives\n+- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-004-B — Authenticator can be disabled\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=false\n+- **WHEN** any request arrives\n+- **THEN** request passes through without token validation\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - Session Management\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-005-A — Session manager creates session\n+\n+- **GIVEN** SessionManager with SessionEnabled=true\n+- **WHEN** a new session is created via session store\n+- **THEN** session ID is generated\n+- **AND** session data is stored with expiry\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-005-B — Session manager cleanup removes expired sessions\n+\n+- **GIVEN** SessionManager with sessions in store\n+- **WHEN** cleanup runs and finds expired sessions\n+- **THEN** expired sessions are removed from store\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-005-C — Session middleware attaches session to request\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a request with valid session cookie\n+- **WHEN** request passes through SessionMiddleware\n+- **THEN** session info is available in request context\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - JWT Authentication\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-006-A — JWT manager creates token\n+\n+- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with HS256 algorithm and secret=\"mysecret\"\n+- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called with user claims\n+- **THEN** a signed JWT token is returned\n+- **AND** token contains correct issuer and audience\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-006-B — JWT manager validates token\n+\n+- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with valid secret\n+- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with a valid token\n+- **THEN** claims are returned without error\n+- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with an expired token\n+- **THEN** error is returned indicating token expiration\n+- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with invalid signature\n+- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid token\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-006-C — JWT middleware enforces authentication\n+\n+- **GIVEN** JWTMiddleware with JWTEnabled=true and JWTAllowQueryParam=false\n+- **WHEN** request without JWT arrives at protected endpoint\n+- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n+- **WHEN** request with valid JWT in Authorization header arrives\n+- **THEN** request is allowed and claims available in context\n+- **WHEN** JWTAllowQueryParam=true and JWT in query param\n+- **THEN** request is allowed\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Router Module - Logging and Metrics\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-007-A — Logger records requests\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Logger middleware is in the chain\n+- **WHEN** HTTP request arrives\n+- **THEN** request details are logged including method, path, duration\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-007-B — Metrics records request stats\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Metrics instance\n+- **WHEN** `IncBackendRequests(backend, status)` is called\n+- **THEN** backend request counter increments\n+- **WHEN** `RecordRequestDuration(method, path, backend, duration)` is called\n+- **THEN** request duration is recorded\n+- **WHEN** `IncErrors(errorType)` is called\n+- **THEN** error counter increments\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Store Module - Store Interface\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-008-A — Store interface contract\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a Store implementation (Valkey or Redis)\n+- **WHEN** all interface methods are called\n+- **THEN** the Store implements the complete Store interface:\n+  - Ping() error\n+  - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n+  - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n+  - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n+  - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error\n+  - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n+  - ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n+  - UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n+  - Close() error\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Store Module - Valkey Store\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-A — Valkey store connects with credentials\n+\n+- **GIVEN** environment variables VALKEY_ADDR and VALKEY_PASSWORD are set\n+- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n+- **THEN** a Valkey client connects successfully\n+- **AND** ping returns \"PONG\"\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-B — Valkey store requires address\n+\n+- **GIVEN** VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n+- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n+- **THEN** error is returned indicating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-C — Valkey store stores sandbox\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo with SessionID and ExpiresAt\n+- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n+- **THEN** sandbox is stored in Valkey\n+- **AND** session is added to expiry index\n+- **AND** session is added to last activity index\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-D — Valkey store retrieves sandbox\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a sandbox was previously stored\n+- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n+- **THEN** correct SandboxInfo is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-E — Valkey store returns error for non-existent session\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a session ID that doesn't exist\n+- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n+- **THEN** ErrNotFound is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-F — Valkey store updates sandbox\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n+- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n+- **THEN** sandbox data is updated\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-G — Valkey store deletes sandbox\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n+- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n+- **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n+- **AND** session is removed from expiry index\n+- **AND** session is removed from last activity index\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-H — Valkey store lists expired sandboxes\n+\n+- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n+- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n+- **THEN** only sandboxes expiring before 'before' are returned\n+- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-I — Valkey store lists inactive sandboxes\n+\n+- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different last activity times\n+- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n+- **THEN** only sandboxes inactive before 'before' are returned\n+- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-J — Valkey store validates input\n+\n+- **GIVEN** nil sandbox passed to StoreSandbox\n+- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"sandbox is nil\" is returned\n+\n+- **GIVEN** sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\n+- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\" is returned\n+\n+- **GIVEN** sandbox with empty SessionID\n+- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"session ID is required\" is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-K — Valkey store updates last activity\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n+- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time)` is called\n+- **THEN** last activity timestamp is updated in index\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-009-L — Valkey store closes connection\n+\n+- **GIVEN** a Valkey store is connected\n+- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n+- **THEN** connection is closed\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Picod Module - Server Initialization\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-010-A — Server creates with valid config\n+\n+- **GIVEN** valid Config and AuthConfig\n+- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n+- **THEN** server instance is returned\n+- **AND** Gin engine is configured\n+- **AND** routes are registered\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-010-B — Server validates config\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Config with invalid values (e.g., negative port)\n+- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n+- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid config\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-010-C — Server sets workspace directory\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Config with Workspace=\"/tmp/test-workspace\"\n+- **WHEN** Server initializes\n+- **THEN** workspace directory is created if not exists\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-010-D — Server creates with empty workspace\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Config with empty Workspace\n+- **WHEN** Server initializes\n+- **THEN** current working directory is used as workspace\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Picod Module - Path Sanitization\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-011-A — Path sanitization allows safe paths\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n+- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"subdir/file.txt\")` is called\n+- **THEN** resolved path within workspace is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-011-B — Path sanitization blocks escape attempts\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n+- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-011-C — Path sanitization blocks absolute paths\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n+- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"/etc/passwd\")` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-011-D — Path sanitization handles symlinks\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\" and symlink /app/link -> /tmp\n+- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"link/sensitive\")` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Picod Module - Authentication\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-012-A — Auth manager loads public key\n+\n+- **GIVEN** AuthConfig with valid RSA public key in PEM format\n+- **WHEN** AuthManager initializes\n+- **THEN** public key is loaded successfully\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-012-B — Auth manager validates JWT\n+\n+- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n+- **WHEN** valid JWT token is validated\n+- **THEN** claims are returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-012-C — Auth manager rejects invalid JWT\n+\n+- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n+- **WHEN** invalid or expired JWT token is validated\n+- **THEN** error is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-012-D — Auth middleware allows public paths\n+\n+- **GIVEN** request to public path like /health\n+- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n+- **THEN** request is allowed without JWT validation\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-012-E — Auth middleware requires auth for protected paths\n+\n+- **GIVEN** request to protected path /api/execute without token\n+- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n+- **THEN** request is rejected with 401\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Picod Module - Execute Handler\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-013-A — Execute handler runs valid command\n+\n+- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]\n+- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** response with stdout=\"hello\", ExitCode=0 is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-013-B — Execute handler fails on empty command\n+\n+- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with empty Command array\n+- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-013-C — Execute handler respects timeout\n+\n+- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"sleep\", \"10\"] and Timeout=\"1s\"\n+- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** response with ExitCode=124 (timeout) is returned\n+- **AND** stderr indicates timeout\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-013-D — Execute handler validates working directory\n+\n+- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with WorkingDir=\"../../../etc\"\n+- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-013-E — Execute handler captures stderr\n+\n+- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"ls\", \"/nonexistent\"]\n+- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** response includes stderr output\n+- **AND** non-zero ExitCode is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-013-F — Execute handler accepts custom environment\n+\n+- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"env\"] and Env={\"TEST_VAR\": \"test\"}\n+- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** response stdout contains TEST_VAR=test\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Picod Module - File Handlers\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-014-A — Upload file handler saves file\n+\n+- **GIVEN** file upload request with valid content\n+- **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** file is saved to workspace\n+- **AND** success response is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-014-B — List files handler returns directory contents\n+\n+- **GIVEN** workspace with multiple files\n+- **WHEN** ListFilesHandler is called\n+- **THEN** list of files is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-014-C — Download file handler serves file\n+\n+- **GIVEN** file exists in workspace\n+- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler is called with path\n+- **THEN** file content is served\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-014-D — Download file handler blocks path escape\n+\n+- **GIVEN** request for file outside workspace\n+- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler processes request\n+- **THEN** request is rejected\n+\n+---\n+\n+### Feature: Picod Module - Health Check and RSA Key Loading\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-015-A — Health check returns healthy status\n+\n+- **GIVEN** Server is running\n+- **WHEN** GET /health is requested\n+- **THEN** response with status \"healthy\" is returned\n+- **AND** HTTP 200 status code\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-015-B — LoadRSAPublicKey parses valid PEM\n+\n+- **GIVEN** valid RSA public key in PEM format\n+- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n+- **THEN** *rsa.PublicKey is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-015-C — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects invalid PEM\n+\n+- **GIVEN** invalid PEM data\n+- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n+- **THEN** error is returned\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-039-015-D — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects non-RSA key\n+\n+- **GIVEN** PEM data containing non-RSA key\n+- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n+- **THEN** error \"public key is not an RSA key\" is returned\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+### Router Module\n+- [ ] AC001: Unit tests for Config initialization and defaults\n+- [ ] AC002: Unit tests for Router creation with various config combinations\n+- [ ] AC003: Unit tests for BackendPool AddBackend, RemoveBackend, GetBackendForRequest\n+- [ ] AC004: Unit tests for HealthChecker Start, Stop, checkBackend\n+- [ ] AC005: Unit tests for RateLimiter Allow, Middleware\n+- [ ] AC006: Unit tests for Authenticator Middleware with enabled/disabled states\n+- [ ] AC007: Unit tests for SessionManager Create, Get, Delete, Cleanup\n+- [ ] AC008: Unit tests for JWTManager GenerateToken, ValidateToken\n+- [ ] AC009: Unit tests for JWTMiddleware with various configurations\n+- [ ] AC010: Unit tests for Logger Middleware\n+- [ ] AC011: Unit tests for Metrics IncBackendRequests, RecordRequestDuration, IncErrors\n+\n+### Store Module\n+- [ ] AC012: Unit tests for Valkey store connection with mocked client\n+- [ ] AC013: Unit tests for StoreSandbox with valid and invalid inputs\n+- [ ] AC014: Unit tests for GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existing sessions\n+- [ ] AC015: Unit tests for UpdateSandbox\n+- [ ] AC016: Unit tests for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n+- [ ] AC017: Unit tests for ListExpiredSandboxes\n+- [ ] AC018: Unit tests for ListInactiveSandboxes\n+- [ ] AC019: Unit tests for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n+- [ ] AC020: Unit tests for Close\n+\n+### Picod Module\n+- [ ] AC021: Unit tests for Server creation with valid and invalid configs\n+- [ ] AC022: Unit tests for setWorkspace\n+- [ ] AC023: Unit tests for sanitizePath with various path inputs\n+- [ ] AC024: Unit tests for AuthManager LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, ValidateToken\n+- [ ] AC025: Unit tests for auth middleware with public/protected paths\n+- [ ] AC026: Unit tests for ExecuteHandler with valid commands, timeout, invalid working dir\n+- [ ] AC027: Unit tests for UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler\n+- [ ] AC028: Unit tests for HealthCheckHandler\n+- [ ] AC029: Unit tests for LoadRSAPublicKey\n+- [ ] AC030: Existing tests in router, store, picod packages remain passing\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Test File Status\n+\n+| Source File | Test File | Status |\n+|-------------|-----------|--------|\n+| router/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+| router/config.go | config_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/route.go | route_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/backend.go | backend_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/health.go | health_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/ratelimit.go | ratelimit_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/session.go | session_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/jwt.go | jwt_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/logging.go | logging_test.go | Complete |\n+| router/metrics.go | (uses existing) | N/A |\n+| store/store.go | (interface only) | N/A |\n+| store/store_valkey.go | store_valkey_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+| store/store_redis.go | store_redis_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+| picod/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+| picod/execute.go | execute_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+| picod/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n+| picod/files.go | files_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+| picod/health.go | health_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Testing Patterns\n+\n+### Mocking Strategy\n+- Use interfaces for dependencies (Store, HTTP clients, etc.)\n+- Create mock implementations for testing using testify/mock\n+- Use gomock or testify.mock for generating mocks\n+\n+### Test File Naming\n+- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n+- Keep tests in same package as code under test\n+- Use `package router` (not `package router_test`)\n+\n+### Table-Driven Tests\n+- Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n+- Example pattern:\n+```go\n+tests := []struct {\n+    name    string\n+    input   string\n+    want    string\n+    wantErr bool\n+}{...}\n+```\n+\n+### Test Coverage Goals\n+- Router module: 70%+ code coverage\n+- Store module: 80%+ code coverage\n+- Picod module: 70%+ code coverage\n+\n+---\n+\n+## References\n+\n+- Router module: `pkg/router/`\n+- Store module: `pkg/store/`\n+- Picod module: `pkg/picod/`\n+- Common types: `pkg/common/types/`\n+\n+## Overview\n+\n This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n \n ## Base Specifications\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n\nThe system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n- **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n- **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n  - `language`: `\"python\"`\n  - `port`: `8080`\n  - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n  - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n  - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n  - `--language` overrides `language`\n  - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n  - `--port` overrides `port`\n  - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n  - `--description` overrides `description`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n- **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n\nThe system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n\n- **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n  - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n  - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n  - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n  - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n- **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n- **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n- **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n- [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n- [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n- [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n- [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n- [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n- [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n- [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n- [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n| PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n| MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n| AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n| DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n\n### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n| entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n| requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n\n### CLI Options Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n|------------|----------------|------|\n| `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n| `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n| `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n| `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n| `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n| `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n| `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n\n---\n\n# Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-038\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n## Reference\n\nBase spec: client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module provides workload management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. It includes:\n- WorkloadManager interface for CRUD operations\n- GC (Garbage Collection) worker for expired resource cleanup\n- Expiration checker for TTL and idle timeout\n- Graceful manager for connection draining\n- Cleanup manager for orphaned resources\n- Batch manager for bulk operations\n- HTTP server with REST API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: CleanupManager Resource Cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-A — CleanupManager deletes orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupServices is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned service resource strings\n- **AND** services with matching owner references should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-B — CleanupManager deletes orphaned configmaps\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupConfigMaps is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned configmap resource strings\n- **AND** configmaps with the annotation `agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete=true` and matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-C — CleanupManager handles retained PVCs\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupPVCs is called with a namespace and owner reference for a PVC with Retain policy\n- **THEN** the PVC should not be deleted\n- **AND** other PVCs with matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-D — CleanupManager cleans orphaned resources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager and a Sandbox object\n- **WHEN** cleanupOrphanedResources is called\n- **THEN** it should clean services, configmaps, and PVCs associated with the sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-E — CleanupManager finds orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** FindOrphanedServices is called with namespace and sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return service names that have no owner references\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-F — CleanupManager CleanupAllResources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** CleanupAllResources is called with a sandbox\n- **THEN** it should clean all associated resources\n\n---\n\n### Feature: BatchManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-A — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes synchronously under threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with fewer than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes synchronously\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with deleted and failed counts\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-B — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes asynchronously over threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with more than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should start async deletion in background\n- **AND** return immediately with all items marked as deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-C — BatchManager deletes stale sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** deleteStaleSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes in Unknown or Failed state older than StaleStateThreshold (1 hour)\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with results\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-D — BatchManager deletes by label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteByLabelSelector is called with a label selector\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes matching the label selector\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-E — BatchManager public methods\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager\n- **WHEN** DeleteAllInNamespace, DeleteByLabelSelector, or DeleteStaleSandboxes are called\n- **THEN** they should delegate to the appropriate handler methods\n\n---\n\n### Feature: WorkloadManager Sandbox Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-A — GetSandboxBySessionID finds AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in an AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-B — GetSandboxBySessionID finds CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in a CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-C — GetSandboxBySessionID returns error when not found\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a non-existent sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return ErrSandboxNotFound\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-D — DeleteSandbox deletes AgentRuntime by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching AgentRuntime\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-E — DeleteSandbox deletes CodeInterpreter by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-F — DeleteSandbox applies force delete\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with Force=true\n- **THEN** it should set GracePeriodSeconds to 0\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-G — DeleteSandbox applies label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with LabelSelector\n- **THEN** it should use the label selector when listing resources\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-H — ListSandboxes returns combined list\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called with namespace and ListOptions\n- **THEN** it should return a SandboxList containing both types\n- **AND** apply label and field selectors correctly\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Server HTTP Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-A — Server health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server instance\n- **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-B — Server readiness check - ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=true\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with status \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-C — Server readiness check - not ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=false\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 503 with status \"not ready\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-D — Server starts and stops cleanly\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with valid config\n- **WHEN** Start() is called\n- **THEN** it should bind to the configured port\n- **AND** Start() should return nil\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-E — Server handles API error mapping\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with a WorkloadManager that returns an error\n- **WHEN** handleError is called with k8s IsNotFound error\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 404 with reason \"NotFound\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-F — Server corsMiddleware sets headers\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server\n- **WHEN** corsMiddleware processes a request\n- **THEN** it should set Access-Control-Allow-* headers\n- **AND** handle OPTIONS preflight requests\n\n---\n\n### Feature: GracefulManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-A — GracefulManager registers connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** RegisterConnection is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should increment\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-B — GracefulManager unregisters connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with an active connection\n- **WHEN** UnregisterConnection is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should decrement\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-C — GracefulManager drains connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** drainConnections is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the draining flag should be set to true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-D — GracefulManager checks if draining\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox marked for draining\n- **WHEN** IsDraining is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** it should return true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-E — GracefulManager gets active connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with registered connections\n- **WHEN** GetActiveConnections is called\n- **THEN** it should return the correct count\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-F — GracefulManager cleans up sandbox state\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox\n- **WHEN** Cleanup is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the sandbox entry should be removed from connections map\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-G — GracefulManager waitForConnections timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with active connections that never drain\n- **WHEN** waitForConnections is called with a short timeout\n- **THEN** it should return an error after timeout\n\n---\n\n### Feature: K8sClient Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-A — K8sClient NewK8sClient with kubeconfig path\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig path\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with the path\n- **THEN** it should return a K8sClient with Clientset, KubernetesClient, and DynamicClient\n- **AND** return nil error\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-B — K8sClient NewK8sClient with in-cluster mode\n\n- **GIVEN** InClusterMode constant\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with InClusterMode\n- **THEN** it should attempt in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-C — K8sClient NewInClusterClient\n\n- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** NewInClusterClient is called\n- **THEN** it should create clients using in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-D — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles tilde\n\n- **GIVEN** a path starting with ~\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should replace ~ with the home directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-E — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles empty path\n\n- **GIVEN** an empty string\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should return the empty string\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Type Helper Functions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-A — NewAPIResponse creates correct response\n\n- **GIVEN** data and metadata\n- **WHEN** NewAPIResponse is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIResponse with Status=\"Success\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-B — NewAPIError creates correct error\n\n- **GIVEN** message, reason, and code\n- **WHEN** NewAPIError is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIError with Status=\"Failure\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-C — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Running condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-D — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps failed state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Failed condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateFailed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-E — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps deleting state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateDeleting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-F — sandboxFromCodeInterpreter maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with Ready=true\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromCodeInterpreter is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n---\n\n### Feature: ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-A — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-B — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-C — ListExpiredSandboxes handles empty namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with resources in a namespace\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with an empty namespace string\n- **THEN** it should list all expired sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Retry Logic\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-A — Retry with exponential backoff\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that fails initially then succeeds\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied\n- **THEN** it should retry with increasing delays\n- **AND** ultimately succeed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-B — Retry stops after max attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that always fails\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied with max attempts\n- **THEN** it should return the last error after exhausting retries\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: All CleanupManager methods must have unit tests covering success and error paths\n- [ ] AC002: All BatchManager methods must have tests with mocked WorkloadManager\n- [ ] AC003: WorkloadManager sandbox operations must have tests with fake clients\n- [ ] AC004: Server HTTP handlers must have tests using httptest\n- [ ] AC005: GracefulManager connection tracking must have unit tests\n- [ ] AC006: K8sClient initialization must have tests for different config modes\n- [ ] AC007: Helper functions (NewAPIResponse, NewAPIError, sandboxFrom*) must have tests\n- [ ] AC008: ListExpiredSandboxes must have tests for both resource types\n- [ ] AC009: Retry logic must have unit tests for backoff behavior\n- [ ] AC010: Existing tests in service_test.go, gc_test.go, expiration_test.go remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| service.go | service_test.go | Complete |\n| gc.go | gc_test.go | Complete |\n| expiration.go | expiration_test.go | Complete |\n| cleanup.go | cleanup_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| server.go | server_test.go | Complete |\n| graceful.go | graceful_test.go | Complete |\n| batch.go | batch_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| client.go | client_test.go | Complete |\n| delete_test.go | N/A | Exists |\n| retry.go | retry_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-039\n- **Module**: `pkg`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n\n1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT\n2. **pkg/store**: Valkey/Redis-backed session and sandbox storage\n3. **pkg/picod**: Pico execution server with command execution and file handling\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Initialization and Configuration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-A — Router creates with default config\n\n- **GIVEN** a nil config is passed to `NewRouter`\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with default configuration values\n- **AND** default listen address is \":8080\"\n- **AND** backend timeout is 30 seconds\n- **AND** rate limiting is disabled by default\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-B — Router creates with custom config\n\n- **GIVEN** a Config with SessionEnabled=true and JWTEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n- **THEN** a Router instance is returned with SessionManager initialized\n- **AND** JWTManager is initialized\n- **AND** SessionHandler is registered for /v1/sessions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-001-C — Router adds and removes backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a Router instance is created\n- **WHEN** `AddBackend(\"backend1\", \"http://localhost:8081\", \"/api\", \"backend-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is added to the pool\n- **WHEN** `RemoveBackend(\"backend1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the backend is removed from the pool\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Backend Pool and Health Checking\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-A — Backend pool routes requests\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with multiple backends registered\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a path matching a backend prefix\n- **THEN** the matching backend is returned\n- **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a non-matching path\n- **THEN** nil is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-002-B — Health checker monitors backends\n\n- **GIVEN** a BackendPool with registered backends\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Start() is invoked\n- **THEN** periodic health checks run at configured interval\n- **WHEN** a backend becomes unhealthy\n- **THEN** the backend is marked as unavailable\n- **WHEN** HealthChecker Stop() is invoked\n- **THEN** health checking stops\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Rate Limiting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-A — Rate limiter allows requests under limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=10 and Burst=20\n- **WHEN** 5 requests arrive in quick succession\n- **THEN** all requests are allowed through\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-B — Rate limiter blocks requests over limit\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=2 and Burst=4\n- **WHEN** 10 requests arrive simultaneously\n- **THEN** requests beyond burst limit are blocked with 429 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-003-C — Rate limiter can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** RateLimiter with enabled=false\n- **WHEN** any number of requests arrive\n- **THEN** all requests pass through without rate limiting\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-A — Authenticator validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=true and AuthToken=\"secret\"\n- **WHEN** request with \"Authorization: Bearer secret\" header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n- **WHEN** request with wrong token arrives\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-004-B — Authenticator can be disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** Authenticator with AuthEnabled=false\n- **WHEN** any request arrives\n- **THEN** request passes through without token validation\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Session Management\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-A — Session manager creates session\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with SessionEnabled=true\n- **WHEN** a new session is created via session store\n- **THEN** session ID is generated\n- **AND** session data is stored with expiry\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-B — Session manager cleanup removes expired sessions\n\n- **GIVEN** SessionManager with sessions in store\n- **WHEN** cleanup runs and finds expired sessions\n- **THEN** expired sessions are removed from store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-005-C — Session middleware attaches session to request\n\n- **GIVEN** a request with valid session cookie\n- **WHEN** request passes through SessionMiddleware\n- **THEN** session info is available in request context\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - JWT Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-A — JWT manager creates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with HS256 algorithm and secret=\"mysecret\"\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called with user claims\n- **THEN** a signed JWT token is returned\n- **AND** token contains correct issuer and audience\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-B — JWT manager validates token\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTManager configured with valid secret\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with a valid token\n- **THEN** claims are returned without error\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with an expired token\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating token expiration\n- **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called with invalid signature\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid token\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-006-C — JWT middleware enforces authentication\n\n- **GIVEN** JWTMiddleware with JWTEnabled=true and JWTAllowQueryParam=false\n- **WHEN** request without JWT arrives at protected endpoint\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401 status\n- **WHEN** request with valid JWT in Authorization header arrives\n- **THEN** request is allowed and claims available in context\n- **WHEN** JWTAllowQueryParam=true and JWT in query param\n- **THEN** request is allowed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Router Module - Logging and Metrics\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-A — Logger records requests\n\n- **GIVEN** Logger middleware is in the chain\n- **WHEN** HTTP request arrives\n- **THEN** request details are logged including method, path, duration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-007-B — Metrics records request stats\n\n- **GIVEN** Metrics instance\n- **WHEN** `IncBackendRequests(backend, status)` is called\n- **THEN** backend request counter increments\n- **WHEN** `RecordRequestDuration(method, path, backend, duration)` is called\n- **THEN** request duration is recorded\n- **WHEN** `IncErrors(errorType)` is called\n- **THEN** error counter increments\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Store Interface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-008-A — Store interface contract\n\n- **GIVEN** a Store implementation (Valkey or Redis)\n- **WHEN** all interface methods are called\n- **THEN** the Store implements the complete Store interface:\n  - Ping() error\n  - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error\n  - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error\n  - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n  - UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n  - Close() error\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Store Module - Valkey Store\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-A — Valkey store connects with credentials\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variables VALKEY_ADDR and VALKEY_PASSWORD are set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** a Valkey client connects successfully\n- **AND** ping returns \"PONG\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-B — Valkey store requires address\n\n- **GIVEN** VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n- **WHEN** `newValkeyStore()` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-C — Valkey store stores sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo with SessionID and ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is stored in Valkey\n- **AND** session is added to expiry index\n- **AND** session is added to last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-D — Valkey store retrieves sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox was previously stored\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** correct SandboxInfo is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-E — Valkey store returns error for non-existent session\n\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that doesn't exist\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** ErrNotFound is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-F — Valkey store updates sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox data is updated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-G — Valkey store deletes sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** sandbox is removed from store\n- **AND** session is removed from expiry index\n- **AND** session is removed from last activity index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-H — Valkey store lists expired sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes expiring before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-I — Valkey store lists inactive sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes with different last activity times\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** only sandboxes inactive before 'before' are returned\n- **AND** maximum of 'limit' results are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-J — Valkey store validates input\n\n- **GIVEN** nil sandbox passed to StoreSandbox\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"sandbox is nil\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"invalid expiry: ExpiresAt is zero\" is returned\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with empty SessionID\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"session ID is required\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-K — Valkey store updates last activity\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in store\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time)` is called\n- **THEN** last activity timestamp is updated in index\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-009-L — Valkey store closes connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a Valkey store is connected\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** connection is closed\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Server Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-A — Server creates with valid config\n\n- **GIVEN** valid Config and AuthConfig\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** server instance is returned\n- **AND** Gin engine is configured\n- **AND** routes are registered\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-B — Server validates config\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with invalid values (e.g., negative port)\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config, authConfig)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-C — Server sets workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with Workspace=\"/tmp/test-workspace\"\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** workspace directory is created if not exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-010-D — Server creates with empty workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** Config with empty Workspace\n- **WHEN** Server initializes\n- **THEN** current working directory is used as workspace\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Path Sanitization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-A — Path sanitization allows safe paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"subdir/file.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** resolved path within workspace is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-B — Path sanitization blocks escape attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"../../../etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-C — Path sanitization blocks absolute paths\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\"\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"/etc/passwd\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-011-D — Path sanitization handles symlinks\n\n- **GIVEN** Server with workspace=\"/app\" and symlink /app/link -> /tmp\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath(\"link/sensitive\")` is called\n- **THEN** error \"access denied: path escapes workspace\" is returned\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Authentication\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-A — Auth manager loads public key\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthConfig with valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** AuthManager initializes\n- **THEN** public key is loaded successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-B — Auth manager validates JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** valid JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** claims are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-C — Auth manager rejects invalid JWT\n\n- **GIVEN** AuthManager with loaded public key\n- **WHEN** invalid or expired JWT token is validated\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-D — Auth middleware allows public paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to public path like /health\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is allowed without JWT validation\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-012-E — Auth middleware requires auth for protected paths\n\n- **GIVEN** request to protected path /api/execute without token\n- **WHEN** request passes through auth middleware\n- **THEN** request is rejected with 401\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Execute Handler\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-A — Execute handler runs valid command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with stdout=\"hello\", ExitCode=0 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-B — Execute handler fails on empty command\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with empty Command array\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-C — Execute handler respects timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"sleep\", \"10\"] and Timeout=\"1s\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response with ExitCode=124 (timeout) is returned\n- **AND** stderr indicates timeout\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-D — Execute handler validates working directory\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with WorkingDir=\"../../../etc\"\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** error response with code 400 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-E — Execute handler captures stderr\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"ls\", \"/nonexistent\"]\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response includes stderr output\n- **AND** non-zero ExitCode is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-013-F — Execute handler accepts custom environment\n\n- **GIVEN** ExecuteRequest with Command=[\"env\"] and Env={\"TEST_VAR\": \"test\"}\n- **WHEN** ExecuteHandler processes request\n- **THEN** response stdout contains TEST_VAR=test\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - File Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-A — Upload file handler saves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file upload request with valid content\n- **WHEN** UploadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** file is saved to workspace\n- **AND** success response is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-B — List files handler returns directory contents\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace with multiple files\n- **WHEN** ListFilesHandler is called\n- **THEN** list of files is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-C — Download file handler serves file\n\n- **GIVEN** file exists in workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler is called with path\n- **THEN** file content is served\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-014-D — Download file handler blocks path escape\n\n- **GIVEN** request for file outside workspace\n- **WHEN** DownloadFileHandler processes request\n- **THEN** request is rejected\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Picod Module - Health Check and RSA Key Loading\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-A — Health check returns healthy status\n\n- **GIVEN** Server is running\n- **WHEN** GET /health is requested\n- **THEN** response with status \"healthy\" is returned\n- **AND** HTTP 200 status code\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-B — LoadRSAPublicKey parses valid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** valid RSA public key in PEM format\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** *rsa.PublicKey is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-C — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects invalid PEM\n\n- **GIVEN** invalid PEM data\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AR-039-015-D — LoadRSAPublicKey rejects non-RSA key\n\n- **GIVEN** PEM data containing non-RSA key\n- **WHEN** `LoadRSAPublicKey(pemData)` is called\n- **THEN** error \"public key is not an RSA key\" is returned\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Router Module\n- [ ] AC001: Unit tests for Config initialization and defaults\n- [ ] AC002: Unit tests for Router creation with various config combinations\n- [ ] AC003: Unit tests for BackendPool AddBackend, RemoveBackend, GetBackendForRequest\n- [ ] AC004: Unit tests for HealthChecker Start, Stop, checkBackend\n- [ ] AC005: Unit tests for RateLimiter Allow, Middleware\n- [ ] AC006: Unit tests for Authenticator Middleware with enabled/disabled states\n- [ ] AC007: Unit tests for SessionManager Create, Get, Delete, Cleanup\n- [ ] AC008: Unit tests for JWTManager GenerateToken, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC009: Unit tests for JWTMiddleware with various configurations\n- [ ] AC010: Unit tests for Logger Middleware\n- [ ] AC011: Unit tests for Metrics IncBackendRequests, RecordRequestDuration, IncErrors\n\n### Store Module\n- [ ] AC012: Unit tests for Valkey store connection with mocked client\n- [ ] AC013: Unit tests for StoreSandbox with valid and invalid inputs\n- [ ] AC014: Unit tests for GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existing sessions\n- [ ] AC015: Unit tests for UpdateSandbox\n- [ ] AC016: Unit tests for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n- [ ] AC017: Unit tests for ListExpiredSandboxes\n- [ ] AC018: Unit tests for ListInactiveSandboxes\n- [ ] AC019: Unit tests for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n- [ ] AC020: Unit tests for Close\n\n### Picod Module\n- [ ] AC021: Unit tests for Server creation with valid and invalid configs\n- [ ] AC022: Unit tests for setWorkspace\n- [ ] AC023: Unit tests for sanitizePath with various path inputs\n- [ ] AC024: Unit tests for AuthManager LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, ValidateToken\n- [ ] AC025: Unit tests for auth middleware with public/protected paths\n- [ ] AC026: Unit tests for ExecuteHandler with valid commands, timeout, invalid working dir\n- [ ] AC027: Unit tests for UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler\n- [ ] AC028: Unit tests for HealthCheckHandler\n- [ ] AC029: Unit tests for LoadRSAPublicKey\n- [ ] AC030: Existing tests in router, store, picod packages remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| router/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| router/config.go | config_test.go | Complete |\n| router/route.go | route_test.go | Complete |\n| router/backend.go | backend_test.go | Complete |\n| router/health.go | health_test.go | Complete |\n| router/ratelimit.go | ratelimit_test.go | Complete |\n| router/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| router/session.go | session_test.go | Complete |\n| router/jwt.go | jwt_test.go | Complete |\n| router/logging.go | logging_test.go | Complete |\n| router/metrics.go | (uses existing) | N/A |\n| store/store.go | (interface only) | N/A |\n| store/store_valkey.go | store_valkey_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| store/store_redis.go | store_redis_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/server.go | server_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/execute.go | execute_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/auth.go | auth_test.go | Complete |\n| picod/files.go | files_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| picod/health.go | health_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n- Use interfaces for dependencies (Store, HTTP clients, etc.)\n- Create mock implementations for testing using testify/mock\n- Use gomock or testify.mock for generating mocks\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Go convention: `*_test.go`\n- Keep tests in same package as code under test\n- Use `package router` (not `package router_test`)\n\n### Table-Driven Tests\n- Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n- Example pattern:\n```go\ntests := []struct {\n    name    string\n    input   string\n    want    string\n    wantErr bool\n}{...}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- Router module: 70%+ code coverage\n- Store module: 80%+ code coverage\n- Picod module: 70%+ code coverage\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Router module: `pkg/router/`\n- Store module: `pkg/store/`\n- Picod module: `pkg/picod/`\n- Common types: `pkg/common/types/`\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n\nThe system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n- **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n- **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n  - `language`: `\"python\"`\n  - `port`: `8080`\n  - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n  - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n  - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n  - `--language` overrides `language`\n  - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n  - `--port` overrides `port`\n  - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n  - `--description` overrides `description`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n- **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n\nThe system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n\n- **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n\n- **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n\n- **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n  - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n  - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n  - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n  - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n- **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n- **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n\n#### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n- **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n- [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n- [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n- [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n- [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n- [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n- [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n- [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n- [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n| PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n| MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n| AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n| DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n\n### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n| entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n| requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n\n### CLI Options Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n|------------|----------------|------|\n| `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n| `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n| `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n| `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n| `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n| `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n| `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n\n---\n\n# Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-038\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n## Reference\n\nBase spec: client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module provides workload management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. It includes:\n- WorkloadManager interface for CRUD operations\n- GC (Garbage Collection) worker for expired resource cleanup\n- Expiration checker for TTL and idle timeout\n- Graceful manager for connection draining\n- Cleanup manager for orphaned resources\n- Batch manager for bulk operations\n- HTTP server with REST API endpoints\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: CleanupManager Resource Cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-A — CleanupManager deletes orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupServices is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned service resource strings\n- **AND** services with matching owner references should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-B — CleanupManager deletes orphaned configmaps\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupConfigMaps is called with a namespace and owner reference\n- **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned configmap resource strings\n- **AND** configmaps with the annotation `agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete=true` and matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-C — CleanupManager handles retained PVCs\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** cleanupPVCs is called with a namespace and owner reference for a PVC with Retain policy\n- **THEN** the PVC should not be deleted\n- **AND** other PVCs with matching owner should be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-D — CleanupManager cleans orphaned resources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager and a Sandbox object\n- **WHEN** cleanupOrphanedResources is called\n- **THEN** it should clean services, configmaps, and PVCs associated with the sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-E — CleanupManager finds orphaned services\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** FindOrphanedServices is called with namespace and sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return service names that have no owner references\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-001-F — CleanupManager CleanupAllResources\n\n- **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** CleanupAllResources is called with a sandbox\n- **THEN** it should clean all associated resources\n\n---\n\n### Feature: BatchManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-A — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes synchronously under threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with fewer than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes synchronously\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with deleted and failed counts\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-B — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes asynchronously over threshold\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with more than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n- **THEN** it should start async deletion in background\n- **AND** return immediately with all items marked as deleted\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-C — BatchManager deletes stale sandboxes\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** deleteStaleSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes in Unknown or Failed state older than StaleStateThreshold (1 hour)\n- **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with results\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-D — BatchManager deletes by label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n- **WHEN** handleDeleteByLabelSelector is called with a label selector\n- **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes matching the label selector\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-002-E — BatchManager public methods\n\n- **GIVEN** a BatchManager\n- **WHEN** DeleteAllInNamespace, DeleteByLabelSelector, or DeleteStaleSandboxes are called\n- **THEN** they should delegate to the appropriate handler methods\n\n---\n\n### Feature: WorkloadManager Sandbox Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-A — GetSandboxBySessionID finds AgentRuntime\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in an AgentRuntime\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-B — GetSandboxBySessionID finds CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a sessionID that exists in a CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** it should return a Sandbox object with correct fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-C — GetSandboxBySessionID returns error when not found\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a non-existent sessionID\n- **THEN** it should return ErrSandboxNotFound\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-D — DeleteSandbox deletes AgentRuntime by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has AgentRuntime with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching AgentRuntime\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-E — DeleteSandbox deletes CodeInterpreter by sessionId\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has CodeInterpreter with matching sessionId label\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with namespace, sessionID, and delete options\n- **THEN** it should delete the matching CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** return nil on success\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-F — DeleteSandbox applies force delete\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with Force=true\n- **THEN** it should set GracePeriodSeconds to 0\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-G — DeleteSandbox applies label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client\n- **WHEN** DeleteSandbox is called with LabelSelector\n- **THEN** it should use the label selector when listing resources\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-003-H — ListSandboxes returns combined list\n\n- **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with a client that has both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListSandboxes is called with namespace and ListOptions\n- **THEN** it should return a SandboxList containing both types\n- **AND** apply label and field selectors correctly\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Server HTTP Handlers\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-A — Server health check endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server instance\n- **WHEN** GET /healthz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-B — Server readiness check - ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=true\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 200 with status \"ok\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-C — Server readiness check - not ready\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with ready=false\n- **WHEN** GET /readyz is requested\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 503 with status \"not ready\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-D — Server starts and stops cleanly\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with valid config\n- **WHEN** Start() is called\n- **THEN** it should bind to the configured port\n- **AND** Start() should return nil\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-E — Server handles API error mapping\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server with a WorkloadManager that returns an error\n- **WHEN** handleError is called with k8s IsNotFound error\n- **THEN** it should return HTTP 404 with reason \"NotFound\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-004-F — Server corsMiddleware sets headers\n\n- **GIVEN** a Server\n- **WHEN** corsMiddleware processes a request\n- **THEN** it should set Access-Control-Allow-* headers\n- **AND** handle OPTIONS preflight requests\n\n---\n\n### Feature: GracefulManager Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-A — GracefulManager registers connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** RegisterConnection is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should increment\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-B — GracefulManager unregisters connection\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with an active connection\n- **WHEN** UnregisterConnection is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the active connection count should decrement\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-C — GracefulManager drains connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager\n- **WHEN** drainConnections is called with a sandboxID\n- **THEN** the draining flag should be set to true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-D — GracefulManager checks if draining\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox marked for draining\n- **WHEN** IsDraining is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** it should return true\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-E — GracefulManager gets active connections\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with registered connections\n- **WHEN** GetActiveConnections is called\n- **THEN** it should return the correct count\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-F — GracefulManager cleans up sandbox state\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with a sandbox\n- **WHEN** Cleanup is called with the sandboxID\n- **THEN** the sandbox entry should be removed from connections map\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-005-G — GracefulManager waitForConnections timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** a GracefulManager with active connections that never drain\n- **WHEN** waitForConnections is called with a short timeout\n- **THEN** it should return an error after timeout\n\n---\n\n### Feature: K8sClient Initialization\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-A — K8sClient NewK8sClient with kubeconfig path\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig path\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with the path\n- **THEN** it should return a K8sClient with Clientset, KubernetesClient, and DynamicClient\n- **AND** return nil error\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-B — K8sClient NewK8sClient with in-cluster mode\n\n- **GIVEN** InClusterMode constant\n- **WHEN** NewK8sClient is called with InClusterMode\n- **THEN** it should attempt in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-C — K8sClient NewInClusterClient\n\n- **GIVEN** running inside a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** NewInClusterClient is called\n- **THEN** it should create clients using in-cluster config\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-D — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles tilde\n\n- **GIVEN** a path starting with ~\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should replace ~ with the home directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-006-E — K8sClient expandKubeconfigPath handles empty path\n\n- **GIVEN** an empty string\n- **WHEN** expandKubeconfigPath is called\n- **THEN** it should return the empty string\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Type Helper Functions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-A — NewAPIResponse creates correct response\n\n- **GIVEN** data and metadata\n- **WHEN** NewAPIResponse is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIResponse with Status=\"Success\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-B — NewAPIError creates correct error\n\n- **GIVEN** message, reason, and code\n- **WHEN** NewAPIError is called\n- **THEN** it should return an APIError with Status=\"Failure\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-C — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Running condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-D — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps failed state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Failed condition\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateFailed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-E — sandboxFromAgentRuntime maps deleting state\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromAgentRuntime is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateDeleting\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-007-F — sandboxFromCodeInterpreter maps running state\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with Ready=true\n- **WHEN** sandboxFromCodeInterpreter is called\n- **THEN** the returned Sandbox should have State=SandboxStateRunning\n\n---\n\n### Feature: ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-A — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired AgentRuntimes\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-B — ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called\n- **THEN** it should return sandboxes that have expired\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-008-C — ListExpiredSandboxes handles empty namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a client with resources in a namespace\n- **WHEN** ListExpiredSandboxes is called with an empty namespace string\n- **THEN** it should list all expired sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Retry Logic\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-A — Retry with exponential backoff\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that fails initially then succeeds\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied\n- **THEN** it should retry with increasing delays\n- **AND** ultimately succeed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-038-009-B — Retry stops after max attempts\n\n- **GIVEN** a function that always fails\n- **WHEN** retry logic is applied with max attempts\n- **THEN** it should return the last error after exhausting retries\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: All CleanupManager methods must have unit tests covering success and error paths\n- [ ] AC002: All BatchManager methods must have tests with mocked WorkloadManager\n- [ ] AC003: WorkloadManager sandbox operations must have tests with fake clients\n- [ ] AC004: Server HTTP handlers must have tests using httptest\n- [ ] AC005: GracefulManager connection tracking must have unit tests\n- [ ] AC006: K8sClient initialization must have tests for different config modes\n- [ ] AC007: Helper functions (NewAPIResponse, NewAPIError, sandboxFrom*) must have tests\n- [ ] AC008: ListExpiredSandboxes must have tests for both resource types\n- [ ] AC009: Retry logic must have unit tests for backoff behavior\n- [ ] AC010: Existing tests in service_test.go, gc_test.go, expiration_test.go remain passing\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| service.go | service_test.go | Complete |\n| gc.go | gc_test.go | Complete |\n| expiration.go | expiration_test.go | Complete |\n| cleanup.go | cleanup_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| server.go | server_test.go | Complete |\n| graceful.go | graceful_test.go | Complete |\n| batch.go | batch_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| client.go | client_test.go | Complete |\n| delete_test.go | N/A | Exists |\n| retry.go | retry_test.go | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- API Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh / v1alpha1`\n- Resources: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter","additions":597,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882602366,"end":1775882602631}}}}
