{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882665605,"sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","part":{"id":"prt_d7adafa2c001pMFDzc5Lc2rJGX","messageID":"msg_d7adaee53001oddWMQI3F8hRJ7","sessionID":"ses_28528da7fffeeEo22z8KG7QLjm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_bb4f6da0503d4ddbb128a99f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-039\n10: - **Module**: `pkg`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n19: \n20: 1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT\n21: 2. **pkg/store**: Valkey/Redis-backed session and sandbox storage\n22: 3. **pkg/picod**: Pico execution server with command execution and file handling\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Requirements\n27: \n28: ### Feature: Router Module - Initialization and Configuration\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: AR-039-001-A — Router creates with default config\n31: \n32: - **GIVEN** a nil config is passed to `NewRouter`\n33: - **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n34: - **THEN** a Router instance is returned with default configuration values\n35: - **AND** default listen address is \":8080\"\n36: - **AND** backend timeout is 30 seconds\n37: - **AND** rate limiting is disabled by default\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: AR-039-001-B — Router creates with custom config\n40: \n41: - **GIVEN** a Config with SessionEnabled=true and JWTEnabled=true\n42: - **WHEN** `NewRouter(config)` is called\n43: - **THEN** a Router instance is returned with SessionManager initialized\n44: - **AND** JWTManager is initialized\n45: - **AND** SessionHandler is registered for /v1/sessions\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: AR-039-001-C — Router adds and removes backends\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** a Router instance is created\n50: - **WHEN** `AddBackend(\"backend1\", \"http://localhost:8081\", \"/api\", \"backend-1\")` is called\n51: - **THEN** the backend is added to the pool\n52: - **WHEN** `RemoveBackend(\"backend1\")` is called\n53: - **THEN** the backend is removed from the pool\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Feature: Router Module - Backend Pool and Health Checking\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: AR-039-002-A — Backend pool routes requests\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** a BackendPool with multiple backends registered\n62: - **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a path matching a backend prefix\n63: - **THEN** the matching backend is returned\n64: - **WHEN** `GetBackendForRequest()` is called with a non-matching path\n65: - **THEN** nil is returned\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: AR-039-002-B — Health checker monitors backends\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** a BackendPool with registered backends\n70: - **WHEN** HealthChecker Start() is invoked\n71: - **THEN** periodic health checks run at configured interval\n72: - **WHEN** a backend becomes unhealthy\n73: - **THEN** the backend is marked as unavailable\n74: - **WHEN** HealthChecker Stop() is invoked\n75: - **THEN** health checking stops\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ### Feature: Router Module - Rate Limiting\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: AR-039-003-A — Rate limiter allows requests under limit\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=10 and Burst=20\n84: - **WHEN** 5 requests arrive in quick succession\n85: - **THEN** all requests are allowed through\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: AR-039-003-B — Rate limiter blocks requests over limit\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** RateLimiter with RPS=2 and Burst=4\n90: - **WHEN** 10 requests arrive simultaneously\n91: - **THEN** requests beyond burst limit are blocked with 429 status\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: AR-039-003-C — Rate limiter can be disabled\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** RateLimiter with enabled=false\n96: - **WHEN** any number of requests arrive\n97: - **THEN** all requests pass through without rate limiting\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 1320. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-039 — Go Unit Testing (router/store/picod)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for three core modules: router, store, and picod.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-039\n- **Module**: `pkg`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube project consists of three main modules requiring unit tests:\n\n1. **pkg/router**: HTTP routing, proxy, health checking, rate limiting, authentication, session management, JWT","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882665593,"end":1775882665603}}}}
